The paper discusses statistical de-anonymization attacks on high-dimensional micro-data, which involves techniques from machine learning, data mining, and privacy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
